    "cross_verification": "The 240 canonical mismatch weights are byte-identical across the two independent tools above (max abs diff 0.0). The 16 PAM weights match AlleleForge's previously-vetted published PAM table. CRISPRitz additionally ships 152 RNA/DNA-bulge entries used only for its indel alignment; those are intentionally excluded here (standard substitution CFD).",
    "key_format": "mismatch keys are the upstream Doench form 'r<guide-RNA-base>:d<complement-of-target-base>,<1-based-position>'; pam keys are the two nucleotides 3' of the N in an NGG PAM."
